If you read a map of New York, you can see streets, important places, and gather knowledge of what it looks like, but you&#8217;re not in New York. Scriptures give you knowledge in the manner of a map.
<br>Q: Is it useful to have a map?
<br>A: It&#8217;s useful if you&#8217;re going to New York. Otherwise, it&#8217;s a load. <span class=date>9/2/79</span>
